18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 690.11 of Title 63, unless there
21 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. There is hereby created the Grants for Recovering,
23 Improving, and Thriving economies program (GRIT). This program
24 shall be administered by the Oklahoma Department of Emergency
Req. No. 12363 Page 1

1 Mana gement. This program shall be for political subdivisions, with
2 populations less than six thousand (6000) people who are directly
3 impacted by events attributing to a Federal Emergency Management
4 Agency (FEMA) declared emergency or disasters. These political
5 subdivisions may apply for a GRIT grant if they are unable to
6 provide the full local match required under the relevant FEMA
7 recovery program. The Department shall promulgate rules to
8 administer the grant program.
9 SECTION 2. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a
10 revolving fund for the Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management
11 to be designated the "Grants for Recovering, Improving, and Thriving
12 Economies Revolving Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not
13 subject to fiscal year limitations, and shall consist of all monies
14 received by the Department from appropriations. All monies accruing
15 to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated and may be
16 budgeted and expended by the Department for the purpose of Grants
17 for Recovering, Improving, and Thriving economies program described
18 in Section 1 of this act. Expenditures from said fund shall be made
19 upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
20 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
21 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
22 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
